Dear John,  and category theorists,=0A=
=0A=
The fact that every category has an opposite introduces =0A=
a symmetry in mathematics that would not be there otherwise. =0A=
The category of sets is not self dual, but a disjoint union of sets =0A=
is a coproduct, dual to a product.  =0A=
=0A=
Thurston does not show esteem for logic.=0A=
Most mathematicians are taking logic for granted; they just use it =0A=
as a part of their natural language. =0A=
It is obvious that human understanding depends on the =0A=
the laws of thought, on logic. =0A=
In a sense, category theory is a branch of mathematical logic,=0A=
since it greatly improves mathematical thinking in general.=0A=
A category theorist might say (not too loudly) that mathematical logic=0A=
is a branch of category theory.=0A=
=0A=
Best,=0A=
andr=E9=0A=
=0A=
